  "2026-04-26T00:31:13.065Z",codex-agent,"Remote telemetry verification 2026-04-26: health endpoint https://pm-cli.unbrained.dev/healthz returned ok true queue pm.telemetry.events; synthetic POST to /v1/events accepted one event with schema_version 1; Grafana endpoint https://pm.unbrained.dev returned authenticated login redirect. Remaining gap observed in local CLI: pm health output does not include telemetry runtime/export status despite operations guidance expecting telemetry visibility."
  "2026-04-26T09:57:39.575Z",codex-agent,"Phase 4b-c remote verification completed on 2026-04-26: stack services healthy, telemetry API/Grafana reachable, Prometheus ingest and Tempo span signals present, Postgres telemetry tables populated, and synthetic UUID event persisted (command=remote-audit-smoke). Added/updated child findings: pm-vhdc (UUID ingestion validation backlog), pm-300m (pm health telemetry diagnostics gap), pm-r9ei (Grafana queue panel selector mismatch)."
  "2026-04-26T14:51:47.449Z",audit-agent,"2026-04-26 audit confirms: Remote telemetry stack fully operational. All 9 containers healthy. 11,414+ events in Postgres. Grafana v11.6.14 accessible. Alloy forwarding Docker logs to Loki and OTLP traces to Tempo. Telemetry API accepts events (HTTP 200). Outstanding gaps: capture_level not enforced, retention_days not enforced, no pm health telemetry check."
  "2026-04-27T19:46:02.711Z",codex-agent,"Telemetry backlog wave 2026-04-27 completed: closed child issues pm-vhdc (UUID boundary validation + worker poison-drain remediation), pm-r9ei (Grafana queue panel query alignment to exporter label model), and pm-pxx0 (local retention_days queue pruning). Evidence artifacts are linked under scripts/prod/telemetry (baseline + per-item execution logs). Final verification includes remote healthz ok, queue depth 0/0, PromQL queue vectors non-empty for patched expressions, and local telemetry/health unit suites passing (34 tests)."
  "2026-04-27T21:29:37.428Z",codex-agent,"Closure-readiness evidence 2026-04-27: parent-filtered lifecycle scans show no remaining active children (pm list-open --parent pm-lnq3 --limit 50 => 0; pm list-in-progress --parent pm-lnq3 --limit 50 => 0) and full delivered lineage remains terminal (pm list-closed --parent pm-lnq3 --limit 50 => 12)."
